Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Failing test: "should apply +50% surcharge for a cursed item"
Expected behavior: quote([{type:"sword", material:"steel", enchantment:0, cursed:true}], {yearsAsCustomer:0}, 1) returns 165
Current error: expected 115 to be 165
Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
const FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_RATE = 1 / 10;

const applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge = (premium: number): number =>
  premium + premium * FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_RATE;

const BASE_PREMIUMS: Record<string, number> = {
  sword: 100, amulet: 60, staff: 80, potion: 40, rune: 25, moonstone: 25,
};

const COMPONENT_TYPES = ["rune", "moonstone"];
const BLOCK_SIZE = 3;
const BLOCK_PREMIUM = 60;

export const quote = (items: Array<{ type: string }>, customer: unknown, contractNumber: number): number => {
  const componentCounts: Record<string, number> = {};
  for (const item of items) {
    if (COMPONENT_TYPES.includes(item.type)) {
      componentCounts[item.type] = (componentCounts[item.type] ?? 0) + 1;
    }
  }
  let totalPremium = 0;
  for (const item of items) {
    if (COMPONENT_TYPES.includes(item.type) && componentCounts[item.type] === BLOCK_SIZE) {
      continue;
    }
    const basePremium = BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type] ?? 0;
    totalPremium += applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge(basePremium);
  }
  for (const type of COMPONENT_TYPES) {
    if (componentCounts[type] === BLOCK_SIZE) {
      totalPremium += applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge(BLOCK_PREMIUM);
    }
  }
  return Math.ceil(totalPremium) + PROCESSING_FEE;
};
```

The problem: the cursed surcharge (50% of base premium) needs to be added to the item's premium. Per the spec:
- Item-specific modifiers (cursed, high enchantment) apply to the base premium of the affected item
- Policy-wide modifiers (first insurance) apply to the policy base premium (sum of all item base premiums WITHOUT item-specific modifiers)

So the calculation should be:
1. Sum up base premiums for all items → policy base premium
2. Add item-specific modifiers (cursed surcharge) per item
3. Add policy-wide modifiers (first insurance surcharge) based on policy base premium
4. Add processing fee

For this test: policy base premium = 100. Cursed surcharge = 50% of 100 = 50. First insurance = 10% of 100 = 10. Total = 100 + 50 + 10 = 160 + 5 fee = 165.

The current implementation applies first insurance per-item during the loop. We need to restructure: compute policy base premium, add item-specific surcharges, then add policy-wide modifiers.

Minimal change: update the item type to include cursed property, compute item-specific surcharges separately, apply policy-wide modifiers to the policy base premium.

IMPORTANT: Don't break existing tests. The previous tests all had cursed: false or no cursed property (components).

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

